<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">825.24/954: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-06T19:00:00-04:00">April 6, 1943—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>403. Your A–364 of March 11.<note n="92" xml:id="d159fn92">Not
                                    printed.</note> Please urge Chilean authorities to announce
                                immediately to the trade the list of non-importable articles, <pb facs="0180" n="168" xml:id="pg_168"/> in accordance with Henry’s
                                and Wilkinson’s understanding that this would be done. In fairness
                                to United States exporters it is desired to publish the list here at
                                once, but announcement by the Chilean Government should take place
                                previously or coincidently. Telegraph reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>